         <section id="abstract" class="article-section article-section--abstract">
          <div id="en_graphical_abstract" class="article-section__content abstract-graphical" lang="en">
           <h2 class="article-section__header">Abstract</h2>
           <a title="Link to full-size image" href="http://api.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/asset/v1/doi/10.1002%2Fanie.201601231/asset/image_m%2Fanie201601231-toc-0001-m.png?l=SkaBT8QEx2qMKFzmpntImnGCSDtbJzr835fdlhWFty8xAHQ3R5K7MJI7Ezn9kz6%2BBW31eUkivduB%0ARKMufxaR1CiYlPOYgkYR" class="figZoom">
            <figure class="abstract-graphical__fig">
             <img class="abstract-graphical__img" alt="original image" title="original image" src="http://api.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/asset/v1/doi/10.1002%2Fanie.201601231/asset/image_n%2Fanie201601231-toc-0001.png?l=SkaBT8QEx2qMKFzmpntImnGCSDtbJzr8ziq10pkzjzK0T9IlRS1A8c%2FglmbmzEp%2FwF97dZrUjcvs%0ACS%2FJ0V6hgQ%3D%3D">
            </figure></a>
           <p>“… <em>Despite the introduction of high-throughput and combinatorial methods that certainly can be useful in the process of catalysts optimization, it is recognized that the generation of fundamental knowledge at the molecular level is key for the development of new concepts and for reaching the final objective of solid catalysts by design</em> …” Read more in the Editorial by Avelino Corma.</p>
          </div>
         </section>
